President Obama announced his intent to nominate Helen Reed-Rowe as Ambassador to the Republic of Palau, Department of State. Reed-Rowe is a career member of the Senior Foreign Service and currently serves as a Senior Advisor to the Office of Performance Evaluation in the Department of State. She has held various positions in Washington and overseas, including Deputy Chief of Mission at the U.S. Embassy in Majuro, Republic of the Marshall Islands. Reed-Rowe holds an M.A. in National Security and Strategic Studies from the Naval War College and a B.A. from the University of Maryland.

President Obama also announced his intent to appoint Harold Varmus as Director of the National Cancer Institute. Varmus is a former Director of the National Institutes of Health (NIH) and co-recipient of the 1989 Nobel Prize in Physiology or Medicine for studies of the genetic basis of cancer. He currently serves as the President of Memorial Sloan-Kettering Cancer Center in New York City. Varmus has a long career in cancer research and has made significant contributions to the field. He holds degrees from Amherst College, Harvard University, and Columbia University's College of Physicians and Surgeons.